text.__SUMMARY__: Prunus javanica is a species of plant in the family Rosaceae. It is found in India, Indonesia, Malaysia, and Myanmar.
text.References: Kalkman, C. (1998). "Prunus javanica". The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. IUCN. 1998: e.T33592A9789617. doi:10.2305/IUCN.UK.1998.RLTS.T33592A9789617.en. Retrieved 22 December 2017.
